[normal]5.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The argument, even fear, expressed by many campaigners that such segregated provision is too difficult, costly or controversial is falsely based.  
[normal]5.1.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]If one takes time to understand the development of facilities to be found in continental countries it can be seen that by adopting the concept of a 
[normal]safe, 
[normal]physically segregated (but on-line) provision
[normal],
[normal] the attainment of the concept may be achieved in a numb
[normal]er of ways, 
[normal]using
[normal] normal processes.  
[normal]Making
[normal] cycling provisions that enable use by anyone is not rocket science.  Any highways engineer could do it
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]perhaps 
[normal]as demonstrated in Cologne where 
[normal]the City Engineer told a group I led
[normal]: “the politicians 
[normal]wanted peopl
[normal]e to be able to use a bike, so this is what we have done …”.  
[normal]5.1.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Compared with the 
[normal]massive 
[normal]funding used to effectively enthrall the population to the car, costs can be negligible.  
[normal]5.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Essentially 
[normal]one
[normal] start
[normal]s
[normal] with 
[normal]the 
[normal]idea
[normal] of 
[normal]direct, coherent, continuous provision and 
[normal]initially 
[normal]separated by (mandatory) lines, (
[normal]with 
[normal]parking control
[normal]s
[normal] 
[normal]outside
[normal] of these mandatory lines
[normal]).
[normal]  Physical segregation 
[normal]can then
[normal] follow as road
[normal] 
[normal]renewal
[normal] take
[normal]s
[normal] place.
[normal]  
[normal]5.2.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The busiest roads are replaced in cities on 
[normal]approximately 10-20 year cycles. 
[normal]W
[normal]ithin a generation or t
[normal]wo, we coul
[normal]d 
[normal]reach
[normal] Denmark's 
[normal]situation now and 
[normal]approach
[normal] the Netherlands' 
[normal]level of provision
[normal].  
[normal]5.2.1.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]T
[normal]he 
[normal]30 year period
[normal] of the now withdrawn 
[normal]‘
[normal]cul-de-sac and dis
[normal]tributor road’ thinking from 1977 
[normal]has been 
[normal]re
[normal]markably effective
[normal] around the country, 
[normal]and thus 
[normal]the country’
[normal]s
[normal] main routes could be transformed 
[normal]in a similar timespan
[normal].  Only thinking is demanded.
[normal]5.2.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Inevitably some special attention will need to applied to major junctions with their tonnes of concrete, but even these need repair, remodeling and rethinking over time.  The period required seems ‘long’ 
[normal]in prospect
[normal], but the renewal process is 
[normal]happening co
[normal]ntinuously,
[normal] 
[normal]within the 
[normal]span
[normal] of a few Parliaments the transformation could be complete.
[normal]5.2.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Changing the new towns and 70s-onwards estates and their distributor road
[normal], if desired,
[normal] is a big design task, 
[normal]some regeneration projects
[normal] 
[normal]mostly involving turning houses a
[normal]round
[normal]!
[normal]  But for London and most of 
[normal]Britain
[normal], making cycling possible for all could be achieved for 
[normal]the proverbial 
[normal]peanuts
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]And
[normal] if we started 'now'
[normal],
[normal] with the decision to make cycling prov
[normal]isions that were useable by all it could become a reality in reasonable
[normal] time.
